<font color="#FF0000">ANOTHER TRY TO PARTICIPATE</font><br>
<tt>Mon May 12  2:50:17 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Just another vet who stumbled onto the site.  I had thought of trying to use the site to place in the public domain some 200 award-winning photographs of children in the Mekong area which I took in 1970.  They have caused quite a bit of discussion over the years in galleries and magazines, but only a handful have ever been seen by more than a few at a time.  I thought that some of you might see some old memories, and others get a better understanding of those we effected, by releasing them.  I downloaded a few of them to your image files.  They never appeared, despite a commitment from the site staff to get them up on the site.  I guess that the energy drain from the site has doomed any resurgent attempts.  Too bad.  Those of us with resources aren't going to put any work into the site if it can't even respond well.  Not much we can do from out here.  
<p><code>-- gfearon@nbn.com  (Gregory Fearon) </code><p>


